plot: The extreme right seen from the inside: its music, leaders, alliances, rites, and the political acceptance that is opening the Italian Nazi-fascists the doors to institutionalized power. The film show the demonstration attended by &"2 million supporters&" summoned by the premier Silvio Berlusconi (together with him, the main leaders of the neo-Fascist coalition), and take you to a kind of Nashville of the extreme right, organized by the leader of Forza Nuova, Roberto Fiore (sentenced to five years for forming a subversive movement) with the participation of activists and political leaders coming from all over Europe.
